just_use run_corpus_v2.py

# label: TOOL
# role: benchmark beginner.py against the random-deal corpus

Reads `corpus/sessions.txt`, fetches each puzzle's
`initial_state` from the DB, runs `beginner.py`, prints a
per-puzzle line + final depth distribution. The
beginner-side counterpart to `corpus_report.py` (which
benchmarks `bfs_solver.py`).

```
python3 run_corpus_v2.py
```

## Pointers

- Snapshot: `corpus/baseline.txt` is the latest beginner
  benchmark output.
